<article class="component article cf">
	

    

    <p><strong>
<h2>Protecting your Privacy</h2>
</strong>
<p>At Bounty, we are 100% committed to protecting the privacy and security of our Bounty Members and visitors to our website.</p>
<p>We want to earn and maintain your trust, and we believe this is essential in order do that.</p>
<p>Bounty has been helping mums to understand, adapt to and enjoy their pregnancy and new family life for more than sixty years, originally providing free Bounty sample packs and in more recent times adding great digital resources like our app and website.</p>
<p>To do this we need to collect certain personal information and we think it&rsquo;s really important that we help you understand the information we collect, how we use it, and how you have control over it.</p>
<p>We hope our Privacy Policy answers any questions you have, but if not, please do get in touch with us by emailing us at <a href="mailto:privacy@bounty.com">privacy@bounty.com</a>.&nbsp; For all our services, the data controller &mdash; the company that&rsquo;s responsible for your privacy &mdash; is Bounty (UK) Limited.</p>
<p>It&rsquo;s likely that we&rsquo;ll need to update this Privacy Policy from time to time and whilst we&rsquo;ll notify you of any significant changes, you&rsquo;re welcome to come back and check it whenever you wish.</p>
<p>This policy was last updated on the: 23/05/18</p>
<strong>
<h2>Your rights</h2>
</strong>
<p>You have a lot of rights relating to your personal information, and we thought we'd start by setting these out for you:</p>
<div>
<ul>
    <li><span>The right to be informed about how your personal information is being used (like this notice!)</span></li>
    <li>The right to access the personal information we hold about you. You can do this by contacting <a href="mailto:privacy@bounty.com">privacy@bounty.com</a></li>
    <li>The right to request the correction of inaccurate personal information we hold about you (although you can probably do most of this through My Profile or by contacting <a href="mailto:privacy@bounty.com">privacy@bounty.com</a>) </li>
    <li>The right to request that we delete your data, or stop processing it or collecting it, in some circumstances</li>
    <li>The right to stop direct marketing messages, which you can do through My Profile, and to change your preferences in respect of the processing of your data at any time</li>
    <li>The right to complain to your data protection regulator &mdash; in the UK, the Information Commissioner&rsquo;s Office</li>
</ul>
<p>If you want to exercise your rights, have a complaint, or just have questions, please contact us.</p>
<p><strong></strong></p>
<strong>
<h2>About your information</h2>
</strong>
<p><strong></strong></p>
<p>Firstly, we will not sell your personal information to anyone. </p>
<p style="margin: 6pt 0cm; vertical-align: baseline;">We do work with a number of service providers who help us to deliver our services to you including the printers who print the beautiful newborn portraits taken in hospital, payment service providers which process payments and delivery companies which deliver Bounty Portrait orders to you. </p>
<p style="margin: 6pt 0cm; vertical-align: baseline;">It is essential that we share certain information with these companies purely to enable us to provide our services to you.</p>
<strong>
<p>Bounty Partners</p>
</strong>
<p>Depending on which communications you have told us you would like to receive, we may, on behalf of other companies with whom we have trusted relationships (Bounty Partners), send you information about their products and services that we think you will be interested in. These communications will come direct from us and your personal data will stay safe and secure with us.</p>
<p>Our team are always looking for new partners that have information, offers and services to help you and your new family on your journey. This may include companies within the following industries/retail sectors:</p>
<ul>
    <li>automotive</li>
    <li>charitable organisations,</li>
    <li>comparison websites</li>
    <li>electricity, gas, water and multi-utility companies</li>
    <li>fashion and leisure goods</li>
    <li>financial services providers</li>
    <li>food producers</li>
    <li>general marketing</li>
    <li>general retailers</li>
    <li>health and welfare</li>
    <li>household goods</li>
    <li>insurance providers</li>
    <li>marketing agencies</li>
    <li>mobile telecommunication companies</li>
    <li>professional photography</li>
    <li>travel and leisure pursuits</li>
</ul>
<p>We always maintain an up to date list of the specific Bounty Partner companies that we are currently working with which can be found <a href="http://www.bounty.com/info/client-list">here</a>.</p>
<p><strong></strong></p>
<strong>
<h2>What kind of information do we collect and why?</h2>
</strong>
<p>We use your information in a number of different ways &mdash; what we do depends on the information. The tables below set this out in detail showing what we do and why we do it</p>
